The paper focuses on evaluating deep neural network models for image classification under quality distortions, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the state-of-the-art performance of deep neural networks on machine vision tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper considers different types of quality distortions, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
